5. making inventory pannel and adding items in databsae



5. Arrow hits player/enemy → -20 HP, red flash, popup "-20"
	Health bars above everyone (green/red fill)
	Dead? Respawn at start.


	AFter multiplayer is added
	Phase 1: DB Table (1 hour)

	CREATE TABLE player_inventory (playerid VARCHAR(50), item_name VARCHAR(50), quantity INT);
	Load on login, save on equip/use/logout.

	Phase 2-3: Inventory UI + E-Key Overlay (1 day)

	Small JPanel overlay (not full screen switch)
	Buttons: "Sword (x3)", "Arrow (x10)", "Potion (x5)"
	Visual: grid with icons + counts.

	Phase 4-5: Inventory Events + ESC/Q Close (Half day)

	"Equip" → sets p1.equippedWeapon = "arrow"
	ESC/Q → hide overlay, resume game.

	Phase 6: Mouse Shoot (HUGE WOW) (1 day)

	Click anywhere → arrow flies toward mouse (3-5 tiles max)
	Yellow dot trails + poof on wall/hit
	Sync: "SHOOT|mouseWorldX|mouseWorldY"

	Phase 7: Chasing Enemies (1-2 days)

	3-5 goblins spawn random
	Detect players in 5-tile radius → chase closest
	Server tracks enemy pos too ("ENEMY_MOVE|ex|ey")

	Phase 8: Enemy Shoots Back (1 day)

	Enemy faces player → shoots slow blob every 2 sec
	Same projectile code, just enemy-origin.

	Phase 9: Projectile Collisions + Health (1 day)

	Arrow hits player/enemy → -20 HP, red flash, popup "-20"
	Health bars above everyone (green/red fill)
	Dead? Respawn at start.
